08/03/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Macedonian Parliamentary Chairman Ljupco Jordanovski began a two-day formal visit to Zagreb on Monday (7 March), meeting with Croatian Parliamentary representatives and Prime Minister Ivo Sanader. 
All agreed there are no open issues between the two countries, while also calling for intensified bilateral economic co-operation. 
Jordanovski and Sanader also agreed that Macedonia and Croatia would continue collaborating actively in the process of Euro-Atlantic integration, particularly within the framework of the Adriatic Charter initiative, which includes Albania. 
Jordanovski meets with President Stipe Mesic on Tuesday. 
(HINA, Makfax - 07/03/05)
